  <name>Reminduck</name>
  <summary>Remember your stuff in an adorably annoying way</summary>
  <description>
    <p>A simple reminder app made to be quick and easy - Reminduck focuses on simple or recurrent reminders with set time and date and nothing else.</p>

    <p>It's perfect if all you want are simple or daily/weekly/monthly reminders. Anything more than that is not achievable by Reminduck right now - but you can help! Open an issue or a pull request if you have any ideas or requests.</p>

    <p>And it quacks.</p>
  </description>
  <releases>
    <release version="2.2.1" date="2025-07-12">
      <description>
        <ul>
          <li>Updated russian translations thanks to @ma12vlad</li>
        </ul>
      </description>
    <release version="2.2.0" date="2025-07-12">
      <description>
        <ul>
          <li>Settings have been moved into their own view</li>
          <li>Right click on the icon and choose "New reminder" to jump immediately in the editor</li>
        </ul>
      </description>
    </release>
    <release version="2.1.0" date="2025-07-06">
      <description>
        <p>✨NEW IN THE POND✨</p>
        <ul>
          <li>FINALLY a quack setting 🦆 You can even preview the sound!</li>
          <li>Added a menu button with a popover</li>
          <li>Added toggle to change notification persistency</li>
          <li>Added buttons to set/remove autostart</li>
          <li>Bugfix: Now "Show Reminders" should display correctly</li>
        </ul>
      </description>
    </release>
    <release version="2.0.5" date="2025-06-30">
      <description>
        <ul>
          <li>Repaired autostart feature</li>
          <li>Updated IT translation by @albanobattistella</li>
          <li>Corrections for appcenter</li>
        </ul>
      </description>
    </release>
    <release version="2.0.0" date="2025-06-28">
      <description>
        <p>🦆🦆The quack is back!🦆🦆 A continuation of Reminduck, with the blessing of its original creator!</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Adapted to modern libraries (GTK4, Flatpak)</li>
          <li>Make the whole window grabbable</li>
          <li>No quack sound yet but that will come</li>
        </ul>
      </description>
    </release>
    <release version="1.6.2" date="2021-11-16">
